title: Cyrtodactylus mcdonaldi
text:
Cyrtodactylus mcdonaldi is a <a href="species">species</a> of <a href="gecko">gecko</a>, a <a href="lizard">lizard</a> in the <a href="Family%20%28biology%29">family</a> <a href="Gekkonidae">Gekkonidae</a>. The species is <a href="Endemism">endemic</a> to <a href="Queensland">Queensland</a> in Australia.
Etymology.
The <a href="Specific%20name%20%28zoology%29">specific name</a>, "mcdonaldi", is in honor of Australian herpetologist .
Habitat.
The preferred natural <a href="habitat">habitat</a>s of "C. mcdonaldi" are <a href="forest">forest</a>, rocky areas, <a href="savanna">savanna</a>, and freshwater <a href="wetlands">wetlands</a>.
Description.
Medium-sized for its <a href="genus">genus</a>, "C. mcdonaldi" may attain a <a href="Snout-vent%20length">snout-to-vent length</a> (SVL) of .
Diet.
"C. mcdonaldi" <a href="Predation">preys</a> mainly upon <a href="invertebrates">invertebrates</a> such as <a href="beetles">beetles</a> and their <a href="larvae">larvae</a>, <a href="Cockroach">roach</a>es, <a href="spider">spider</a>s, and <a href="scorpion">scorpion</a>s.
Reproduction.
The <a href="Modes%20of%20reproduction">mode of reproduction</a> of "C. mcdonaldi" is unknown.
